caption: Saturday night date night.. Great choice. Food was outstanding. Service was fast and friendly.  The bill was more than fair. The chocolate cake that I somehow found room to eat part of was delicious. It was busy, but no real delays. Two thumbs up. Thank you.
Reservations at a different restaurant didn't work out. They squeezed us in and as always the food was simply amazing. They put their own twist on Italian, but the taste is absolutely amazing!
The place and service were great!  The lasagna and garlic bread were unique but very good.

Besides my reservation not showing up. Which I had a screenshot of the confirmation. The place was nice. Although very very packed. Luckily we were given a nice corner table away from the large groups all around. The food was amazing & the owner was very nice & offered complimentary shots. The prices were pretty good. Their drinks ehhhh not so much. Got a tiny martini for $12 when it definitely was worth about $8. Will go back but during the weekday since it was too packed for me.
Excellent food in a great atmosphere.  They go out of there way to make you feel at gome!
The food here is incredible here I highly recommend you should try them out when you get the chance to. They have an excellent menu selection at that.

Nice casual dining restaurant in downtown Buffalo. Food was good especially the salads (Farmer & Spinach) had unique ingredients and were delicious. Our server Mitchell was friendly and looked after us very well. Our only question about this restaurant is when we checked online for available tables we were told nothing was available between 4 pm and 7 pm so had an early dinner (Lunch menu) at 3:30 and the place was not very busy when we left at 5. What's up with that? We almost didn't go because of that.

Wow!!! What an amazing place. Food was absolutely tasty. It is located 20 minutes away from Niagara Falls, the parking is located 2 min away. I highly recommend to check out the place. I know I will be coming back to this place during my next visit.
The food is amazing here and they have a great menu selection to go with it. I'd ordered here for the first time last night and I'm still thinking about it.

I went to Osteria 166 on a Friday night with my fiancée for my birthday dinner. We were greeted at the door with the welcome sound of live music and the friendly vibe of the owner and his staff, who seemingly did everything in their power to make sure our night was perfect. From the mouthwatering food to the large selection of craft beers and variety of desserts, we got everything we came for and more. Our waitress Sam was so helpful when it came to our questions about the menu and it seemed like everyone working that night had such an upbeat positive energy. Do yourself a favor and check this little gem out for yourself!

First class in every sense of the word. The owner was very accommodating and the entire staff was beyond awesome. Extremely well run restaurant, atmosphere was perfect and the food was out of this world. My fiancée ordered the sea bass and it was one of the best pieces of fish we had ever tried. I ordered the eggplant Milanese and it was cooked to perfection. Everything was so fresh and the entire staff/food/ambience made sure we had no choice but to come back and try everything else on the menu!

Absolutely delicious , authentic Italian cuisine !!! Great stuff 🎈delicious dessert! Awesome pizza ,authentic carbonara. Very friendly and competent service. Good food, large portions. Homemade pasta and sauces, traditional. Nice wine selections at reasonable value. Nice wine selection.

I had such a great time here with my fiance . The food was amazing and the staff could not have been more friendly. We were in town to see the Falls and drove to Osteria 166 because we were looking for a good meal and we were more than satisfied.Absolutely delicious , authentic Italian cuisine !!! Great stuff 🎈delicious dessert! Awesome pizza ,authentic carbonara

We ordered the Meatball and the risotto bites for our appetizers. The meatball is a must try in my opinion. It is so good! For our entree, I ordered the pork tomahawk. It was so good and the portion size was big. The sauce was on point. Highly recommend! My boyfriend ordered the rigatoni bolognese and he enjoyed it. But I have to say the pork tomahawk came out on top. Recommended!
The food is delicious! One of the best sauces I've ever had. If you like the old time Buffalo architecture this place will not disappoint.  Good wines, great staff. Will definitely eat here again.
This place is great! The meatball is a must have if at all possible. Chef jon is the man!!
Excellent food and service. Thank you

The first time I was here was restaurant week. My boyfriend and I came back here for our anniversary dinner. We really wanted to try the food on the regular menu. I called and made reservations which I highly recommended. We went kinda of early for dinner but by the time we finished our food, it was getting busy.  We ordered the Meatball and the risotto bites for our appetizers. The meatball is a must try in my opinion. It is so good! For our entree, I ordered the pork tomahawk. It was so good and the portion size was big. The sauce was on point. Highly recommend! My boyfriend ordered the rigatoni bolognese and he enjoyed it. But I have to say the pork tomahawk came out on top.
Incredible food was very good great menu awesome waitresses great service I will go back

We have never been disappointed with Osteria 166!!  Friday nights in warm weather are where we love to be, listening to the live music with friends.  Wine selection is fabulous and their menu never disappoints:  always something new and fun to try!  Nick, the owner, stops by all of the tables to say hi and may end up chatting and sharing one of his many interesting stories about their food, wine, his family...  You'll feel right at home here!
Delicious food  2 meals for both of us. Called ahead. Curb side pick up

Food was excellent!  Service was good as well.

just not the same.....food over cooked, portions smaller than normal

Went for live music on patio and for dinner. Excellent service and very good food. I will go again.

This place is one of the best spots in Buffalo for perfect Carbonara.

First time I ate their food, it was ordered and sent to the office building where I work. I had the Wagyu Burger (with the Beyond Meat patti) and the fries with sprinkled parm. The entire meal was honestly fantastic.  With COVID going on, I called to ask a few questions regarding ordering for pickup for another day. The gentleman who helped me on the phone with all 6 or so questions was very patient and helpful. He was more than willing to make suggestions and do his best to come up with solutions to what I needed. I had to hold more than once for him to ask someone, which I was more than happy to do, and he didn't seem at all bothered by this.  I'm looking forward to ordering more from them soon and hope to visit their restaurant on site in the future! Absolutely 5 star in every way!
Fantastic food, did curbside pick up, they were on time, food we well packed and everything was perfect.

Food was so terrible I wish I could give them zero stars. My wife got a steak that was about 95 percent fat and not even edible. It was charred on the outside like the grill had never been cleaned. I got chicken parm which was ok, but the pasta it came with tasted like a 50 cent can of spaghettios. Additionally I got a side of risotto which wasn’t even cooked properly it had hard pieces in it. One of the worst meals I ever had in my life.

We went for early dinner, seated in the front where bar is, nice atmosphere. Good menu selection and a bit unique, I had the Wild Board Parpadelle, it was excellent, found the grapes interesting and unique dish, my spouse had the cutlet sandwich with fries, which was freshly pounded and tasted great. We both had a glass of nice red wine, wine list is good with nice quality wine selection. Definitely on our map to go back for a nice full eve dinner!
The Buffalo style calamari is amazing. Atmosphere amazing. All of the food is amazing.
There's a reason Bradley Cooper chose to come here on his visit to the a Queen City.  It's a cool joint with great beer selections and quality bartenders.

Ranging from Nick and Alyssa to Mirinda and the server staff, everyone treats you as though they've known you forever.  Me, my wife and two of our friends went out for restaurant week. The RW menu was awesome. For $20.19 you get an app, an entree and either a dessert or glass of wine. If you wanna get real crazy , you could get a bottle of wine for $20.19. Overall, as usual, the food was incredible. Not a single complaint. If you're looking for great food at a great place with great people, visit O. They always take care of family :)

I still love Osteria, they've improved their pizza and it's all still pretty tasty but the one complaint I have is that the Olive Oil they use now has been stepped on more than cocaine from the bartender at the Pink. The oil simply tastes bad and ruins the flavor of the pizza and anything else it touches, you can tell it's extremely low quality and probably like 5% actual olive oil. This is an Italian restaurant and a pretty good one at that so why would they choose such awful Olive Oil? Makes no sense to me.

We turned around and went back in and bellied up to the bar for a couple of drinks. The bartenders were super friendly and fun. Beautiful restaurant and busy bar. The brunette bartender who was working when we ate here was busting her *ss the whole time we were here. She offers great service, jokes and quick drinks. Great Italian comfort food. The scallops were delicious as was the fried brussel sprouts that we had for appetizers. I went with Chicken Picata for my main and it was awesome. Everyone else in our group loved what they ordered. Would gladly return if I found myself in Buffalo again.

Last week I brought my 92 year old, wheelchair bound friend to Osteria for lunch.  With her age and infirmity, it is no small feat to dine in public.  As a precaution, I telephoned ahead to inquire if the establishment was wheelchair accessible and I was assured it WAS. Our service was mediocre and slow and at times the server was inappropriately condescending in her speech to my guest.  My Panini was hard as a brick and the server was unable to make the espresso I ordered. After our meal, my friend needed to use the ladies room.  Imagine our horror and outrage to discover there were stairs in the hall leading to the ladies room. I asked another server if there was a ramp to place on the stairs and was rudely told no, it was not the restaurant's issue as it merely rented space in the building.  Thankfully a wonderful patron assisted in lifting the wheelchair up the stairs so my friend could use the bathroom and be spared the indignity of incontinence in public. NO staff offered to help. I would give the establishment a negative rating if possible .Callously indifferent to the disabled elderly. Shameful.

Had a great time at osteria 166! My boyfriend and I recently moved to the area and I am originally from buffalo. My friends all recommended osteria and I heard a lot of good things so decided to give it a try. We called on a Saturday and they were fully booked on reservations for the dining room, which was understandable but we decided to go and try sitting at the bar. Got a spot around 7:30pm. The bartenders were so fun and super attentive, to the point they replaced dirty napkins and refilled drinks/waters every time they got about halfway, without even us noticing. They gave great recommendations for places to eat and drink in the area as well. We ordered the Auntie Kims Pasta Fagiole soup which was by far the best I think we've ever had! I also ordered the raviolis and my boyfriend ordered the chicken parm. He is a huge chicken parm guy and said it was in his top 3 best hes ever had. Highly recommend this place, very cool atmosphere, great staff, and amazing food/drinks. This will definitely be a regular spot for us now!
